      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The core tension you've identified is precisely the friction between textual fidelity and evolving societal understandings of rights. Critics argue that deviating from the historical intent risks judicial overreach, effectively allowing unelected judges to legislate from the bench. However, proponents of dynamic interpretation argue that rights themselves are not static concepts and must be understood in the context of contemporary threats to liberty. Ignoring text and history entirely, they caution, risks rendering the Constitution an irrelevant relic unable to protect modern citizens.",
